Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Slice @sweet potatoes{2} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Remove and discard any large stems
from @kale{4%oz}; chop into bite-size pieces. Halve, peel, and finely dice
@shallot{1/2}(finely diced). Place @black peppercorns{1%tablespoon} in a
#zip-close bag{} and crush with a #heavy-bottomed pan{} or #rolling pin{}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss sweet potatoes with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon},
half the @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), a couple big
pinches of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{to taste}.

Arrange on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer. Roast on the top rack until browned
and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While sweet potatoes roast, place kale in bowl used for sweet potatoes and lightly
season with salt. Using your hands, massage kale (similar to how you would knead
dough) until leaves are tender, ~{1%minute}.

> To make kale even more tender, add a drizzle of olive oil along with the salt
> before massaging.

Set aside.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with remaining
garlic powder, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If chicken begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium and cover after
> chicken is flipped. Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{}. Turn off heat;
rinse and wipe out pan.

== Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add minced shallot; cook,
stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @water{1/4%cup}, @chicken demi-glace{1}, and @crushed peppercorns{1/2%tsp};
bring to a simmer; cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{1-3%minutes}.
Remove from heat.

Stir in @crème fraîche{2%tablespoon}, half the @honey dijon dressing{3%oz}, and
@butter{1%tablespoon} until butter is melted. Taste and season with salt.

== Kale-Apple Salad ==

Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}(thinly sliced).

To bowl with kale, add apple, @dried cranberries{1%oz}, @sunflower seeds{1/2%oz},
half the @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, and remaining dressing to taste; toss to coat.
Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, sweet potatoes, and salad between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining parmesan over salad and serve.